  "electricalConnections": [
    {
      "type": "power",
      "source": "battery_pack",
      "target": "motor_driver",
      "voltage": "12.8V Standard (4S) / Max 14.6V Charge Voltage. High current capability for propulsion. Ensure heavy gauge wire used. Overcurrent protection via internal BMS. Nominal 12V is the minimum working voltage. Output protected by 40A fuse. Connect to BATT_POS and BATT_NEG inputs. Check polarity before connecting battery. Do not reverse polarity as the driver lacks protection. Use XT60 connectors for reliable mechanical link. Voltage monitor active via MCU telemetry loop. Estimated peak current draw under stall is 30A. Efficiency typically >95% under load. Operation range -20C to 60C. Rated for industrial outdoor use. Primary energy reservoir for full autonomy. Connect parallel sense lead to MCU for voltage monitoring. Keep wires short to minimize EMI interference. Ensure motor driver is mounted for cooling airflow. Terminal screws torqued to 0.5Nm for secure contact. Wire size 12AWG recommended for power leads. Battery BMS will cut off at 10.0V discharge limit. Charge using dedicated LiFePO4 balance charger only. Do not puncture or expose to high impact. Mechanical mounting via velcro straps in chassis. Ground reference shared across all system components. Main disconnect switch required in series with POS. Power distribution block recommended for multiple loads. Check continuity before first power-up sequence. No visible damage to insulation during inspection. Standard battery for mobile robot research platforms. High cycle life >2000 cycles at 80% DOD. Low self-discharge rate suitable for standby. Safe chemistry for forest corridor operations. Connect ground last to avoid spark discharge. Thermal fuse integrated in battery housing for safety. End of life disposal via recycling center. Maintain 50% charge during long term storage. Use separate logic power if possible for noise. Combined system ground at the battery negative terminal. Verify voltage with multimeter before mating connectors. Use gold plated connectors for low contact resistance. Avoid excessive vibration to internal cells of pack. Proper ventilation required for peak load cooling. Monitor SOC via shunt or voltage divider circuit. Always charge in a fireproof container or area. High quality cells selected for maximum reliability. Built-in thermal protection in motor driver stage. Compatible with Raspberry Pi power distribution rails. Check battery terminal connections for tightness monthly. Grounding lug connected to metal robot chassis. Ensure all connections are moisture resistant for IP65. Use heat shrink tubing on all exposed terminals. Primary power feed to high power motor bus. Connect power first, then logic signals in sequence. Use isolated grounds if noise causes sensor errors. Maintain clean battery terminals to prevent oxidation. Replace pack if casing shows swelling or leaks. Keep away from high voltage lines above the bot. EMI shielding recommended for long wire runs. 12V8V12A"
